# FIFA Ticket Hub Project Analysis

Welcome! This report provides a detailed breakdown of the **FIFA Ticket Hub** codebase, its architecture, database design, user flow, and configuration.

---

## 🏗️ 1. Project Overview & Architecture

The **FIFA Ticket Hub** is a multi-role web application designed for browsing, inquiring about, and managing ticket packages for the FIFA World Cup 2026. 

```mermaid
graph TD
    Client[React Frontend - client/] -->|tRPC Queries & Mutations| Express[Express Server - server/]
    Express -->|Read/Write| Postgres[(PostgreSQL Database)]
    Express -->|Fallback| Memory[(In-Memory Data Fallback)]
    Client -->|Direct API| EmailJS[EmailJS API - Ticket Verification]
    Client -->|Direct Link| WhatsApp[WhatsApp Web/App - Direct Messaging]
```

### Key Architectural Traits
* **tRPC Stack**: Type-safe end-to-end communication between the React frontend and Express backend without boilerplate REST endpoints.
* **Database Fallback Pattern**: The backend database helper ([server/db.ts](file:///c:/Users/USER/Desktop/School/fifa/server/db.ts)) is written defensively. If PostgreSQL is down or unconfigured (`DATABASE_URL` is empty), the application falls back to local in-memory mock data for matches and ticket packages, allowing development to proceed offline.
* **Modern CSS**: Built with the brand new **Tailwind CSS v4** (utilizing `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin and `@theme` configuration directives inside [client/src/index.css](file:///c:/Users/USER/Desktop/School/fifa/client/src/index.css)).

