## 🗄️ 2. Database Schema

The database design relies on four principal tables defined in [POSTGRES_SETUP.sql](file:///c:/Users/USER/Desktop/School/fifa/POSTGRES_SETUP.sql):

### 1. `users` Table
Stores user metadata and authorization roles.
* `id` (serial, PK)
* `openId` (varchar, Unique) — Login identifier (e.g. `local:email@example.com`)
* `name` / `email` / `loginMethod`
* `role` (varchar, default `'user'`) — Restricted to `'admin'` or `'user'`
* `lastSignedIn` / `createdAt` / `updatedAt`

### 2. `matches` Table
Fixture list with location details and global availability status.
* `id` (serial, PK)
* `matchNumber` (integer)
* `team1` / `team2` (varchar) & codes (`team1Code`, `team2Code`)
* `stadium` / `city` / `country`
* `matchDate` (timestamp)
* `stage` (`match_stage` Enum: `'group'`, `'round_of_16'`, `'quarter_final'`, `'semi_final'`, `'final'`)
* `group` (varchar, nullable)
* `availability` (`match_availability` Enum: `'available'`, `'limited'`, `'sold_out'`)

### 3. `ticketPackages` Table
Available tier packages for a specific match.
* `id` (serial, PK)
* `matchId` (integer, FK referencing matches)
* `category` (`ticket_category` Enum: `'Category 1'`, `'Category 2'`, `'Category 3'`, `'Category 4'`)
* `price` (numeric(10,2))
* `quantity` (integer)
* `quantitySold` (integer, default `0`)
* `benefits` (text)
* `seatType` (varchar)

### 4. `customerInquiries` Table
Submissions from users interested in booking tickets.
* `id` (serial, PK)
* `name` / `email` / `phone`
* `matchId` (integer, nullable)
* `ticketCategoryId` (integer, nullable)
* `message` (text)
* `status` (`inquiry_status` Enum: `'new'`, `'contacted'`, `'resolved'`)

